The paper deals with communication systems and feedback mechanisms, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of multiple input multiple output (MIMO) channels and frequency division duplex (FDD) systems suggests that the paper may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The study of achievable diversity multiplexing tradeoff and the evaluation of training and feedback protocols are related to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of i.i.d. Gaussian codebooks and the analysis of the joint probability of SNR exponents suggest that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Communications (cs.COM) sub-categories.
